    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hello @mswilson4040 \r\n\r\nThe refine function that is provided doesn't return a promise by design. It is however non blocking and it shouldn't block the input. This is the same methods that are used to implement all the widgets  in InstantSearch.js. For example using [in the e-commerce demo, the input is not blocked](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/examples/e-commerce/).\r\n\r\nIf you want to listen to listen to the results update, you need to go a level deeper and use the helper. You can use it directly from InstantSearch by [making a custom widget](https://community.algolia.com/instantsearch.js/v2/guides/custom-widget.html) or by [using it alone](https://community.algolia.com/algoliasearch-helper-js/).",
